definition.value: An enone that is hept-1-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 3.
A monoterpenoid that is propanal substituted by a 4-methylcyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 2.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-pydiflumetofen.
A decanoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of decanoc acid (capric acid) with the alcoholic hydroxy group of isobutanol.
A 6beta-hydroxy steroid that is androst-4-ene-3,17-dione substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 6.
A dioxolane that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 4 and 5 respectively.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a dodecasaccharide derivative consisting of a tetrasaccharide chain of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues, all linked sequentially (1->4), to the beta-D-mannose residue of which are also linked beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl and beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl units via (1->6) and (1->3) linkages respectively.
A beta-ocimene that consists of octa-1,3,6-triene bearing two methyl substituents at positions 3 and 7 (the 3Z-isomer).
A fatty acid ethyl ester of 4-octenoic acid.

A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of N-methoxy-1-(2,4,6-trichlorophenyl)propan-2-amine.
3-(difluoromethyl)-N-methoxy-1-methyl-N-[1-(2,4,6-trichlorophenyl)propan-2-yl]pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of pydiflumetofen.
3-(difluoromethyl)-N-methoxy-1-methyl-N-[1-(2,4,6-trichlorophenyl)propan-2-yl]pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of pydiflumetofen.

A carboxylic ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group  of (1R,3R)-3-[(1Z)-2-chloro-3,3,3-trifluoroprop-1-enyl]-2,2-dimethylcyclopropanecarboxylic acid with the hydroxy group of [(2-methyl-1,1'-biphenyl)-3-yl]methanol.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having a 6-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3.
An methyl ketone that is octan-2-one carrying a double bond at position 7.
A methyl ketone heptan-2-one carrying a double bond at position 4.
An alpha-diketone that is hexane substituted by oxo groups at positions 2 and 3 respectively.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N(2)-acyl-L-glutamine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major structure at pH 7.3.
A cyclic dicarboxylic anhydride that is furan-2,5-dione substituted by at position 3 by a  carboxymethyl group and a hexyl group at position 4.
An olefinic compound that octan-2-ol carrying a double bond at position 7.
A tetrahydrofurandione that is succinic anhydride substituted by  a methyl group at position 3.
An inhibitor of the SMAD3 protein.

An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 6,7-dimethoxy-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline with the carboxy group of (2E)-3-(1-methyl-2-phenyl-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-3-yl)acrylic acid.
An alkene that is tridecane carrying a double bond at position 2.
An ammonium ion resulting from the addition of a proton to the free base of SIS3.
A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by an octyl group at position 2.
A 3-hydroxy steroid that is 17beta-estradiol substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 15.
An olefinic compound that is hept-5-en-1-ol substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 6 respectively.
A methyl ketone that is acetone substituted by an  isopropoxy group at position 1.
A dioxolane that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted by a 1-phenylethyl group at position 2.
A cyclic acetal that is pentane in which the carbon atoms at positions 1 and 3 are replaced by oxygen atoms respectively.
A 7alpha-hydroxy steroid that is 17beta-estradiol substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 7.
A methyl ketone that is butan-2-one substituted by a cyano group at position 3.
An alkatetraene that is 1,3,5,7-octatetraene substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 6 respectively.
A member of the class of benzenes that is benzene substituted by a decan-3-yl group.
A 4-hydroxy steroid that is estrone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An amino heptasaccharide in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to D-galactose.
A member of the class of tetralins that is tetralin substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 1 and 6 respectively.
A 6alpha-hydroxy steroid that is estrone substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 6.
A N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as icosanoyl.
A member of the class of 1-benzofurans that is the 2,3-dihydroderivative of benzofuran.
A very long-chain omega-6 fatty acid that is tetratriacontapentaenoic acid having five double bonds located at positions 16, 19, 22, 25 and 28 (the 16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z-isomer).
An aldehyde that is furan substituted by a formyl group at position 3.
An amino nonasaccharide in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to D-galactose.
An aldehyde that is thiophene substituted by a formyl group at position 3.
A very long-chain omega-6 fatty acid that is hexatriacontanoic acid having five double bonds located at positions 18, 21, 24, 27 and 30 (the 18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z-isomer).

An amino oligosaccharide that is an undecaasaccharide derivative in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to D-galactose.
A monohydroxypyridine that is pyridine in which the hydrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
